  "title": "Transport Planner #81009",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Traffic Engineering</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Transport Planner</strong></li><li>Working Location: Ubi</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Monday – Friday, 9.00am – 6.00pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic salary + AWS + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and support studies for road design works and Traffic Layout Plans (TLP) / Traffic Control Plans (TCP).</li><li>Prepare Setting Out Plans (SET), Cross Longitudinal Section (CLS) drawings, and Traffic Control Plans (TCP) / Temporary Layout Plans (TLP) that meet relevant design standards for submission and approval.</li><li>Support projects related to Project Safety Review (PSR), traffic management, and Transport Impact Assessment (TIA), including preparation of technical reports.</li><li>Provide professional traffic-related advice to developers, consultants, and other agencies.</li><li>Use software such as AutoCAD, Civil 3D and AutoTurn for design and analysis tasks.</li><li>Assist in projects or company-related activities in locations where the company has operations or business interests, which may require occasional travel.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Civil Engineering or Traffic / Transportation Engineering.</li><li>Preferably 2–3 years of experience in traffic or transportation-related work.</li><li>Able to draft SET, CLS drawings, and TCP / TLP in line with applicable design standards.</li><li>Knowledge of PSR, traffic management, TIA studies and preparation of technical reports will be an advantage.</li><li>Proficient in AutoCAD, Civil 3D and AutoTurn; knowledge of SIDRA software will be an advantage.</li><li>Certificate from a recognised Road Safety Reviewer course will be an advantage.</li><li>Candidates with substantial relevant experience may be considered for more senior roles.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81009 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
